                "name": "Fast Healing",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A cinder wolf heals 1 point of damage every round that it resists a point or more of fire damage, so long as it has at least 1 hit point. This fire must be from an external source, not from a cinder wolf\u2019s fiery bite."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Fiery Body",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "A cinderwolf inflicts 1d4 points of fire damage when it bites a foe in addition to the normal bite damage. In any round that the cinderwolf resists at least one point of fire damage, it gains fast healing 3."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Trip",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A cinder wolf that hits with a bite attack can attempt to trip the opponent (+3 check modifier) as a free action without making a touch attack or provoking an attack of opportunity. If the attempt fails, the opponent cannot react to trip the cinder wolf."
